 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-axxrd","title":"[CONFORMANCE] fcp-oauth OAuth2 authorization-code + PKCE flow (RFC 6749 §4.1 + RFC 7636)","description":"fcp-oauth currently has ZERO conformance coverage in crates/fcp-conformance/tests/
(grep confirmed: no test file references fcp_oauth or oauth2). The crate implements
RFC 6749 OAuth 2.0 and RFC 7636 PKCE; both specs have enumerable MUST clauses
that belong in a conformance mirror.

**Spec citations:**
- RFC 6749 §4.1 Authorization Code Grant
  - §4.1.1: authorization request URL construction (response_type=code, client_id, redirect_uri, state)
  - §4.1.2: authorization response (code + state MUST echo; on error return error+state)
  - §4.1.3: access token request (grant_type=authorization_code, code, redirect_uri, client_id)
  - §4.1.4: access token response (MUST include access_token, token_type; MAY include expires_in, refresh_token, scope)
- RFC 7636 §4.1: verifier charset [A-Z][a-z][0-9]-._~, length 43..=128
- RFC 7636 §4.2: code_challenge = BASE64URL(SHA256(verifier)) for S256, verifier itself for plain
- RFC 7636 §4.6: server MUST transmit error \"invalid_grant\" when code_verifier mismatches
- RFC 6749 §10.12: state parameter prevents CSRF; servers MUST bind state to session

**Proposed test structure** (one conformance file per spec chunk):
- crates/fcp-conformance/tests/oauth2_auth_code_flow_conformance.rs
  - RFC-6749-4.1.1: authorization URL contains required params
  - RFC-6749-4.1.2: callback parsing echoes state + code on success, error + state on failure
  - RFC-6749-4.1.2: mismatched state → StateMismatch error (test against AuthorizationCallback::validate)
  - RFC-6749-4.1.4: TokenResponse with only access_token + token_type validates
  - RFC-6749-4.1.4: empty access_token rejected with EmptyTokenField error
  - RFC-6749-10.12: empty expected_state rejected (security property)
- crates/fcp-conformance/tests/pkce_conformance.rs (RFC 7636)
  - §4.1: verifier length matrix (42, 43, 128, 129; accept/reject)
  - §4.1: verifier charset matrix (each forbidden char rejected)
  - §4.2: known-answer vectors for S256 challenge derivation (RFC 7636 §B gives a golden vector)
  - §4.2: plain method challenge == verifier

**Oracle strength:** RFC-level (strongest) — deterministic test vectors derived from the RFC itself.

**Cross-reference:** fuzz_oauth_token_response, fuzz_oauth_callback_url, fuzz_pkce_verifier
all land April 2026 (cod_4 / SunnyMoose) — they find crashes; this bead finds spec divergences.

**DoD:**
- Both test files compile + pass cleanly on CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/fcp-swarm-pX
- Each test tagged with RFC clause ID in the function name (e.g. rfc7636_4_1_verifier_length_matrix)
- At least one known-answer vector from RFC 7636 §B included
- DISCREPANCIES.md entry if any intentional divergence (e.g. stricter validation than RFC requires)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-23T18:26:48.573021Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-23T19:36:27.444285Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T19:36:27.443925Z","close_reason":"Added two conformance test binaries under crates/fcp-conformance/tests: pkce_conformance.rs (12 tests covering RFC 7636 §4.1 verifier length+charset, §4.2 S256/Plain derivation, Appendix B known-answer) and oauth2_auth_code_flow_conformance.rs (11 tests covering RFC 6749 §4.1.1 authorize URL, §4.1.2 success + error callback semantics, §4.1.4 token-response shape, §10.12 CSRF state-binding including empty expected_state defense-in-depth, §3.3 space-separated scope list, plus RFC 7636 §4.3 challenge/method in auth URL). All 23 new tests green. Added fcp-oauth + url to fcp-conformance dev-dependencies.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-ayc","title":"fcp.hubspot: Reporting and dashboards","description":"# fcp.hubspot - HubSpot CRM & Marketing Platform Connector

