+{"id":"flywheel_connectors-r3ygj","title":"[REVIEW-P5][HIGH] fcp-webhook::Ed25519Verifier::verify accepts malleable signatures","description":"crates/fcp-webhook/src/signature.rs:206-219 verifies attacker-controlled webhook signatures with ed25519_dalek::Verifier::verify instead of verify_strict. The hardened verifier path elsewhere in the workspace uses verify_strict to reject non-canonical / malleable signatures. On this webhook path, bytewise-distinct signatures over the same payload can still verify, which breaks any downstream dedupe, audit, or cache logic that assumes an accepted signature encoding is unique. Real behavior should use strict Ed25519 verification for untrusted webhook signatures and add a regression test for a non-canonical signature that must fail.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-23T20:42:13.241885Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-23T20:47:39.094772Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T20:47:39.094278Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":2833,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-r3ygj","author":"jemanuel","text":"Resolved in commit 7ddcda16.

Fix: swap ed25519_dalek::Verifier::verify → verify_strict at signature.rs:219 for the untrusted webhook-signature path. verify_strict rejects both high-S malleable signatures (S >= L per RFC 8032 §5.1.7) and mixed-order public-key points. Brings fcp-webhook in line with the rest of the workspace (fcp-crypto, fcp-bootstrap) which already use verify_strict on untrusted inputs.

Regression test test_ed25519_rejects_malleable_high_s_signature:
1. Signs a payload normally; captures canonical (R || S).
2. Constructs the malleation S' = S + L (mod 2^256) via little-endian byte-wise add with carry — the Ed25519 group order L is embedded as a literal constant with a citation comment.
3. Asserts the S bytes actually differ and no 256-bit overflow occurred.
4. Positive control: the canonical signature still verifies.
5. Core assertion: verify() returns InvalidSignature on the (R || S+L) malleation.

Verified: cargo test -p fcp-webhook — 573/573 pass (465 lib + 102 integration + 6 no_mock + 1 ignored).

— cod_4 / SunnyMoose","created_at":"2026-04-23T20:47:38Z"}]}
